01 FEB 95

AMEMBASSY MOSCOW

SUBJECT: IMI:  CUSTOMS REGULATIONS ON IMPORTS OF
PASSENGER VEHICLES TO RUSSIA

1.  SUMMARY.  USFCS MOSCOW IS RECEIVING A NUMBER
OF INQUIRIES FROM U.S. BUSINESSES SEEKING
CLARIFICATION ON CUSTOMS REGULATIONS GOVERNING
IMPORTS OF PASSENGER VEHICLES INTO RUSSIA.
RELEVANT GOVERNMENT OF RUSSIA CUSTOMS REGULATIONS
ARE OFTEN DIFFICULT TO ACCESS.  AND, INFORMATION
CONCERNING CUSTOMS PROCEDURES EMANATING FROM
DIFFERENT SOURCES OUTSIDE OF GOVERNMENT CHANNELS
TEND TO CREATE CONFUSION.  THE FOLLOWING REPORT
INTENDS TO CLARIFY THIS ISSUE AND PROVIDES
INFORMATION BASED ON SPECIFIC ARTICLES FROM THE
RUSSIAN FEDERATION CUSTOMS CODE AND OTHER CUSTOMS
REGULATIONS AS A REFERENCE.  END SUMMARY.

2.  IMPORTERS OF PASSENGER VEHICLES ARE DIVIDED
INTO TWO CATEGORIES:  JURIDICAL ENTITIES (FURTHER
COMPANIES), AND PHYSICAL PERSONS (FURTHER
INDIVIDUALS).  THE IMPORT REGULATIONS APPLIED ON
THESE TWO CATEGORIES OF IMPORTERS DIFFER.
------------------------------------------
PASSENGER VEHICLES IMPORTED BY INDIVIDUALS
------------------------------------------
3.   ACCORDING TO CUSTOMS ORDER NUMBER 416 OF
AUGUST 15, 1994:

A)   INDIVIDUALS IMPORTING VEHICLES NOT FOR
PRODUCTION OR ANY COMMERCIAL ACTIVITY (BUT FOR
PERSONAL USE) SHOULD PAY EITHER FULL RANGE OF
IMPORT DUTIES (IMPORT TARIFF, VAT, AND EXCISE
TAX), OR THEY SHOULD PAY 5 EUROPEAN CURRENCY UNIT
(ECU) EQUIVALENT PER 1 CUBIC CENTIMETER (CC) OF
ENGINE SIZE (PARA 2.3 OF CUSTOMS ORDER 416).

B)   INDIVIDUALS, PERMANENT RESIDENTS OF THE
RUSSIAN FEDERATION WHO STAY ABROAD FOR OVER SIX
MONTHS WITHOUT INTERRUPTION ARE ELIGIBLE TO IMPORT
ONE VEHICLE WITHOUT PAYING IMPORT TAXES, EXCEPT
NEW VEHICLES WITH ENGINE SIZE OVER 1,800 CC
(PARA 2.4).

C)   INDIVIDUALS, MOVING TO RUSSIA FOR PERMANENT
STAY FROM OTHER COUNTRIES ARE EXEMPT FROM IMPORT
DUTIES FOR ONE VEHICLE, EXCEPT NEW VEHICLES WITH
ENGINE SIZE OVER 1,800 CC (PARA 2.8).

D)   INDIVIDUALS, RESIDENTS OF FOREIGN COUNTRIES
ARE EXEMPT FROM IMPORT DUTIES FOR TEMPORARY IMPORT
OF ONE VEHICLE FOR A PERIOD NOT EXCEED TO ONE YEAR
AND ONLY FOR PERSONAL USE OR USE BY THE MEMBERS OF
THE FAMILY OF THIS INDIVIDUAL (PARA 2.9).

E)   INDIVIDUALS SHOULD SUBMIT TO CUSTOMS
OFFICIALS A CUSTOMS DECLARATION WHICH INCLUDES THE
RETAIL COST OF THE VEHICLE.  APPLICANT SHOULD ALSO
SUBMIT DOCUMENTS WHICH PROVE THE VALIDITY OF THE
COST.  CUSTOMS OFFICIALS MIGHT AGREE OR DISAGREE
WITH THE SUBMITTED COST OF THE VEHICLE.  IF
CUSTOMS OFFICIALS DISAGREE, THEY WILL EVALUATE THE
COST THEMSELVES BASED ON PRICE INFORMATION
AVAILABLE AT THE CUSTOMS.  THE IMPORTER CAN
DISPUTE THIS DECISION AND APPLY FOR ANOTHER
EVALUATION (PARA 5.1-5.4).

F)   THERE ARE CUSTOMS FEES CHARGED FOR THE
CUSTOMS PROCEDURE.  IT IS 0.1 PERCENT OF THE
DECLARED CUSTOMS COST OF THE VEHICLE.  THIS FEE IS
PAYABLE IN RUBLES (LOCAL CURRENCY).  THERE IS ALSO
AN ADDITIONAL FEE OF 0.05 PERCENT OF THE DECLARED
CUSTOMS COST AND IS PAYABLE IN HARD CURRENCY.
VEHICLES IMPORTED FOR INDUSTRIAL OR OTHER
COMMERCIAL USE ARE NOT CHARGED AN ADDITIONAL FEE
(PARA 5.5).

