---------------------------------------
TEMPORARY IMPORTS OF PASSENGER VEHICLES
---------------------------------------
5.   CUSTOMS ORDER NUMBER 1276 DATED NOVEMBER 10,
1994, DEALS WITH THE TEMPORARY IMPORT OF GOODS
(INCLUDING CARS) BY REPRESENTATIVES OF FOREIGN
FIRMS OPERATING IN RUSSIA.  IT SAYS THAT:

A)   REPRESENTATIVES OF FOREIGN FIRMS, BANKS, AND
OTHER ORGANIZATIONS WHICH ARE ACCREDITED IN THE
RUSSIAN FEDERATION ARE EXEMPT FROM ALL IMPORT
TAXES ON TEMPORARY IMPORTS OF PRODUCTS TO BE USED
ONLY BY THIS ENTITY AND NOT FOR RESALE (PARA 1).
B)   THE PERIOD OF TEMPORARY IMPORT IS SET BY THE
CUSTOMS OFFICIALS ON THE BASIS OF DURATION OF
ACCREDITATION (PARA 2).

6.   COMPANIES, OTHER THAN THOSE ACCREDITED, AS
DISCUSSED ABOVE, MIGHT ENJOY FULL OR PARTIAL
IMPORT TAX RELIEF UNDER REGULATION PROVIDED IN
CUSTOMS ORDER NUMBER 328 OF APRIL 25, 1994 WHICH
STATES THAT:

A)   TEMPORARY IMPORTS OF PRODUCTS LISTED IN
ATTACHMENT 1 OF SUBJECT CUSTOMS ORDER ARE EXEMPT
FROM ALL IMPORT TAXES IF THE PRODUCT REMAINS IN
RUSSIA LESS THAN ONE YEAR (PARA 1).  THE FOLLOWING
ARE SOME TYPES OF PRODUCTS FROM THE LIST OF
ATTACHMENT 1 WHICH MIGHT BE APPLIED TO VEHICLES:

-    VEHICLES TO BE USED FOR INTERNATIONAL
     TRANSPORTATION OF PASSENGERS AND CARGO, AS
     WELL AS SPARE PARTS AND EQUIPMENT FOR THESE
     PARTICULAR VEHICLES (PARA 1 OF ATTACH.)
-    PRODUCTS FOR EXPOSITION AT THE TRADE SHOWS,
     TRADE FAIRS, INTERNATIONAL EVENTS, SUCH AS
     CONFERENCES, SEMINARS, AND NOT FOR RESALE
     (PARA 3)
-    SAMPLES OF PRODUCTS IMPORTED ONLY FOR THE
     PURPOSE OF ATTRACTING CUSTOMERS.  THE SAMPLES
     SHOULD REMAIN A PROPERTY OF THE FOREIGN
     ENTITY, NOT USED FOR RESALE, AND THE NUMBER
     OF SAMPLES SHOULD NOT EXCEED TWO UNITS OF THE
     SAME TYPE (PARA 10).
-    PRODUCTS IMPORTED FOR THE PURPOSE OF TESTING,
     EXPERIMENTS, EXPOSITION OF QUALITIES AND
     CHARACTERISTICS OF THE PRODUCT, AND NOT FOR
     RESALE (PARA 13).
-    PRODUCTS IMPORTED FOR THE PURPOSE OF SPORT
     COMPETITIONS, SPORT SHOWS, AND TRAINING, IF
     THESE PRODUCTS REMAIN PROPERTY OF FOREIGN
     ENTITY (PARA 16).

B)   TEMPORARY IMPORTED PRODUCTS OTHER THAN THOSE
SPECIFIED IN PARA A OR THOSE SPECIFIED IN PARA A
BUT WITH TEMPORARY USE EXTENDED BEYOND ONE YEAR,
ENJOY A PARTIAL IMPORT TAX RELIEF.  IN THIS
INSTANCE, A CUSTOMS CHARGE OF 3 PERCENT OF THE
TOTAL COST OF THE PRODUCT WILL BE ASSESSED EACH
MONTH.  TOTAL COST EQUALS ORIGINAL PRODUCT PRICE
PLUS ALL IMPORT TAXES.  ADVANCED ASSESSMENT OF UP
TO THREE MONTHS MAY BE REQUESTED. IF THE PRODUCT
IS RE-EXPORTED, THESE FEES ARE NOT RETURNED.  IF
THE TEMPORARY IMPORTED PRODUCT HAS TO BE SOLD, THE
MONTHLY FEES WHICH HAVE ALREADY BEEN PAID BY THAT
TIME ARE INCLUDED INTO IMPORT TAXES TO BE CHARGED
BY THE CUSTOMS (PARA 2-6 OF CUSTOMS ORDER 328).

---------------
VAT EXEMPTION
---------------
ACCORDING TO CUSTOMS ORDER NUMBER 30 OF JANUARY 4,
1994, PRODUCTS IMPORTED INTO RUSSIA AS A
CONTRIBUTION TO AUTHORIZED CAPITAL OF ENTERPRISES
WITH FOREIGN INVESTMENT ARE EXEMPT FROM VALUE
ADDED TAX DURING A ONE YEAR PERIOD FROM THE MOMENT
OF ENTERPRISE REGISTRATION (PARA 1.1).

